			"body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai -->\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nStartup and runtime flows now remove leftover temporary `.crypted` files. A new Resource.cleanupCryptedFiles() is invoked during application startup and after decryption; decrypt and upload paths were changed to properly await moves and to remove temporary encrypted files only when appropriate.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Startup Cleanup** <br> `packages/lib/BaseApplication.ts`|Calls `Resource.cleanupCryptedFiles()` after wiring the DecryptionWorker event handler and in the initial startup path to remove leftover `.crypted` files from previous sessions.|\n|**Decryption & Resource Cleanup** <br> `packages/lib/models/Resource.ts`|`decrypt` now awaits move of failed decrypt attempts, removes the encrypted `.crypted` file after successful decryption when appropriate, and adds `public static async cleanupCryptedFiles()` to scan the resources directory and delete stale `.crypted` files.|\n|**Upload Cleanup** <br> `packages/lib/Synchronizer.ts`|During UPLOAD, computes whether a blob was already encrypted and deletes the local temporary encrypted blob file only when the blob was freshly encrypted by the client.|\n\n## Sequence Diagram(s)\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    autonumber\n    actor User\n    participant App as BaseApplication\n    participant Worker as DecryptionWorker\n    participant ResourceModel as Resource\n    participant FS as FileSystem\n\n    User->>App: Start application\n    App->>Worker: Wire decryption event handler\n    App->>ResourceModel: Resource.cleanupCryptedFiles()\n    ResourceModel->>FS: Scan resources dir for *.crypted\n    FS-->>ResourceModel: List of .crypted files\n    ResourceModel->>FS: Remove leftover .crypted files\n    FS-->>ResourceModel: Removal results\n    ResourceModel-->>App: Cleanup complete\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<!--